event.title: the completion of the Rideau Canal Waterway in 1832

data.event: With the completion of the Rideau Canal Waterway in 1832, steamboats and barges carrying raw materials such as cordwood, maple syrup, potash, cheese, tanned hides and salt beef were a common sight.
The village of Portland took its name in 1843 from William Cavendish-Bentinck, 3rd Duke of Portland.
